headline: Clean Energy to Launch New Freightliner X15N Demo Truck Program at ATA’s MCE in San Diego
summary: NEWPORT BEACH, Calif., October 22, 2025--Clean Energy Fuels Corp. (NASDAQ: CLNE), the largest provider of renewable natural gas (RNG) for the transportation industry, has announced the launch of its second heavy-duty truck demo program, featuring the 2026 Freightliner Cascadia Gen 5 day cab equipped with the Cummins X15N natural gas engine.

headline: 3 Cash-Producing Stocks We Keep Off Our Radar
summary: A company that generates cash isn’t automatically a winner. Some businesses stockpile cash but fail to reinvest wisely, limiting their ability to expand.
